### Randomized Controlled Trials (RCTs)     ||||||||
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34377527/> | Wahls et al           | 2021 | 77 (38/39)   | Multiple Sclerosis     | 24 weeks  | Wahls vs Swank              | Fatigue score: Wahls: -42%, Swank: -31% (both p<0.0001), Quality of Life score: Wahls: +27-31%, Swank: +16-22% (all p<0.05)                                                                    | 10.1177/20552173211035399
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32213121/> | Lee et al             | 2021 | 15 (6/4/4)   | Multiple Sclerosis     | 12 weeks  | Wahls vs keto vs usual      | Fatigue score: Wahls: -60ish%, (p<0.02), mental Quality of Life score: Wahls: +24%, usual: -18% (both p>0.10)                                                                                  | 10.1080/07315724.2020.1734988
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30050374/> | Irish et al           | 2017 | 17 (8/9)     | Multiple Sclerosis     | 3 months  | Wahls vs usual diet         | Fatigue score: Wahls: -33%, usual: +05% (p<0.05); physical Quality of Life score: Wahls: +18ish%, usual: -03% (p=0.05)                                                                         | 10.2147/DNND.S116949
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27235022/> | Otten et al           | 2017 | 32 (16/16)   | Type 2 Diabetes        | 12 weeks  | Paleo +/- HIIT/str. train   | Insulin sensitivity +45% for both (p<0.001), fat mass: paleo -5.7 kg, paleo+ex -6.7 kg (both p<0.001)                                                                                          | 10.1002/dmrr.2828
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27216013/> | Fontes-Villalba et al | 2016 | 13 crossover | Type 2 Diabetes        | 2x3 mo    | Paleo vs Diabetes           | Fasting leptin 31% lower on Paleo vs. diabetes diet (p=0.023). fasting insulin 26% lower on paleo vs. diabetes diet (p=0.266)                                                                  | 10.1186/s12933-016-0398-1
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25828624/> | Masharani et al       | 2015 | 24 (14/10)   | Type 2 Diabetes        | 14 days   | Paleo vs ADA                | Insulin sensitivity: paleo: +18% (p=0.09) American diabetes assoc. diet: +16% (p=0.1). Improvements correlated significantly to severity in Paleo (r=0.63, p=0.02) but not ADA (r=0.39, p=0.3) | 10.1038/ejcn.2015.39
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23890471/> | Jonsson et al         | 2013 | 13 crossover | Type 2 Diabetes        | 2x3 mo    | Paleo vs Diabetes           | Paleo: 20% more satiating per calorie (p=0.004).                                                                                                                                               | 10.1186/1475-2891-12-105
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21118562/> | Jonsson et al         | 2010 | 29 (14/15)   | Type 2 Diabetes        | 12 weeks  | Paleo vs Mediterranean      | Paleo: 56% more satiating per calorie (p=0.03). Fasting leptin: -35% vs. -18% (p=0.04)                                                                                                         | 10.1186/1743-7075-7-85
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19604407/> | Jonsson et al         | 2009 | 13 crossover | Type 2 Diabetes        | 2x3 mo    | Paleo vs Diabetes           | Fasting insulin: Paleo: -46%, Med: -3% (p=0.07), OGTT glucose: -12% vs. -9% (p=0.046), OGTT insulin -17% vs -0% (p=0.13)                                                                       | 10.1186/1475-2840-8-35
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17583796/> | Lindeberg et al       | 2007 | 29 (14/15)   | Ischemic Heart         | 12 weeks  | Paleo vs Mediterranean      | OGTT glucose: paleo: -26% vs med -7% (p=0.001), OGTT insulin: -30% vs. -13% (p=0.13)                                                                                                           | 10.1007/s00125-007-0716-y
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25304296/> | Boers et al           | 2014 | 32 (18/14)   | Metabolic Syndrome     | 2 weeks   | Paleo vs Dutch guidelines   | Metabolic syndrome score: paleo: -27% vs dutch: +7% (p=0.01), blood pressure systolic/diastolic -7%/-9% vs -4%/-3% (p=0.02/p=0.04)                                                             | 10.1186/1476-511X-13-160
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28440046/> | Blomquist et al       | 2017 | 70 (35/35)   | Obese                  | 24 mo     | Paleo vs Diabetes           | Android fat decreased more in PD (p=0.009 at 6mo); hs-CRP decreased (p=0.001 at 24mo).                                                                                                         | 10.1002/oby.21815
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26786351/> | Otten et al           | 2016 | 70 (25/16)   | Obese                  | 24 mo     | Paleo vs Low-Fat            | Insulin resistance: Paleo: -2%, LF: +1%, diastolic blood pressure: -2% vs. +2%. (p-values not given, but claimed significance on paleo from-baseline)                                          | 10.1038/ijo.2016.4
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24473459/> | Mellberg et al        | 2014 | 70 (35/35)   | Obese                  | 24 mo     | Paleo vs NNR                | Fat mass -6.5 vs -2.6 kg at 6mo (p<0.001); TG lower in PD (p<0.001 at 6mo, p=0.004 at 24mo).                                                                                                   | 10.1038/ejcn.2013.290
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27223304/> | Genoni et al          | 2016 | 39 (22/17)   | Overweight             | 4 weeks   | Paleo vs AGHE               | Fat mass -2.14 vs -0.46 kg (p<0.01), waist circumference -3.35 vs. -1.55 cm (p<0.0.1)                                                                                                          | 10.3390/nu8050314
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33844651/> | Fitzgerald et al      | 2021 | 43 (21/22)   | General                | 8 weeks   | Diet+lifestyle vs None      | Age-associated methylation patterns decreased 3.23 years vs controls (p=0.018); TG -25% (p=0.009).                                                                                             | 10.18632/aging.202913
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25661189/> | Bligh et al           | 2015 | 19 crossover | General                | 180 min   | Paleo meals vs WHO Ref      | GLP-1 +20% on isocaloric paleo (p=0.003) and PYY +6% (p=0.011); increased reported satiety.                                                                                                    | 10.1017/S0007114514004012
### Within-Subject Control Trials           ||||||||
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26003334/> | Pastore et al         | 2015 | 20           | Hypercholesterol       | 4 mo each | AHA & Paleo                 | Weight: AHA: -1.9kg, Paleo: -9.3kg (p<0.001). TC, LDL, TG all decreased and HDL increased much more on Paleo (all p<0.001)                                                                     | 10.1016/j.nutres.2015.05.002
### Single-Arm Studies                      ||||||||
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24476345/> | Bisht et al           | 2014 | 20           | Multiple Sclerosis     | 12 mo     | Multimodal Wahls Protocol   | Fatigue (FSS) reduced (p<0.001); mental/physical QoL improvements.                                                                                                                             | 10.1089/acm.2013.0188
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28394724/> | Lee et al             | 2017 | 20           | Multiple Sclerosis     | 12 mo     | Multimodal Wahls Protocol   | Anxiety (BAI) p=0.001-0.02, depression (BDI) p<0.0001-0.09, cognitive function improved; diet dosage most predictive.                                                                          | 10.1080/07315724.2016.1255160
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/6373464/>  | O'Dea                 | 1984 | 10           | Type 2 Diabetes        | 7 weeks   | Traditional hunter-gatherer | Fasting glucose normalized; marked TG reduction; metabolic improvement.                                                                                                                        | 10.2337/diab.33.6.596
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28858071/> | Konijeti et al        | 2017 | 15           | Inflammatory Bowel     | 11 weeks  | Autoimmune Protocol (diet)  | 73% clinical remission; CRP/calprotectin improvement.                                                                                                                                          | 10.1097/MIB.0000000000001221
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31275780/> | Abbot et al           | 2019 | 16           | Hashimotos Thyroiditis | 10 weeks  | Autoimmune Protocol (diet+) | 70% avg. symptom decrease; 29% avg. CRP decrease.                                                                                                                                              | 10.7759/cureus.4556
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37772528/> | Ihnatowicz et al      | 2023 | 28           | Hashimotos Thyroiditis | 12 weeks  | Autoimmune Protocol (diet)  | Relative -78% fatigue, -87% depression, many improvements                                                                                                                                      | 10.26444/aaem/166263
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35811518/> | Toups et al           | 2022 | 25           | Alzheimers/Dementia    | 9 mo      | Precision medicine (diet+)  | MoCA score +3 points (p<0.0001); 80% improved or stable.                                                                                                                                       | 10.3233/JAD-215707
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37355891/> | Sandison et al        | 2023 | 34           | Alzheimers/Dementia    | 6 mo      | Individualized (diet+)      | MoCA score +3 points (p<0.001)                                                                                                                                                                 | 10.3233/JAD-230004
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37858222/> | Berntson et al        | 2023 | 12           | Juv. Idio. Arthritis   | 4 weeks   | Specific Carbohydrate Diet  | Interview study; families reported perceived health benefits.                                                                                                                                  | 10.1186/s12969-023-00914-8
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34112181/> | Berntson et al        | 2021 | 16           | Juv. Idio. Arthritis   | 4 weeks   | Specific Carbohydrate Diet  | Significant reduction in joint morning stiffness and pain.                                                                                                                                     | 10.1186/s12969-021-00577-3
<https://www.mdpi.com/2673-9992/18/1/10>    | McNeill et al         | 2023 | 9            | Rheumatoid Arthritis   | 8 weeks   | Autoimmune Protocol (diet)  | RAPID3 -1.54 (2.53->0.99), 4/9 clinically meaningful (>1.2 reduction); fatigue 4.44->1.11, sleep 3.77->1.22, pain 3.27->1.38.                                                                  | 10.3390/msf2023018010
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23414424/> | Ryberg et al          | 2013 | 10           | Overweight             | 5 weeks   | Paleo diet                  | Liver TG -49%, weight -4.5 kg, diastolic BP -7 mmHg.                                                                                                                                           | 10.1111/joim.12048
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17522610/> | Osterdahl et al       | 2008 | 14           | General                | 3 weeks   | Paleo diet                  | Weight -2.3 kg (p<0.001), SBP -3 mmHg (p=0.03), PAI-1 -72% (p=0.02).                                                                                                                           | 10.1038/sj.ejcn.1602790
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19209185/> | Frassetto et al       | 2009 | 9            | General                | 10 days   | Paleo diet                  | -72% HOMA insulin resistance, -69% fasting insulin                                                                                                                                             | 10.1038/ejcn.2009.4
